.TH "drm_connector_attach_scaling_mode_property" 9 "drm_connector_attach_scaling_mode_property" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_connector_attach_scaling_mode_property \- attach atomic scaling mode property
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_connector_attach_scaling_mode_property
.BI "(struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "u32 scaling_mode_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connector" 12
connector to attach scaling mode property on.
.IP "scaling_mode_mask" 12
or'ed mask of BIT(DRM_MODE_SCALE_\*).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is used to add support for scaling mode to atomic drivers.
The scaling mode will be set to \fIdrm_connector_state.picture_aspect_ratio\fP
and can be used from \fIdrm_connector_helper_funcs->atomic_check\fP for validation.

This is the atomic version of \fBdrm_mode_create_scaling_mode_property\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative errno on failure.
